  <p>
    A septic installation is a large, long-lived investment, and the difference between a smooth
    project and a frustrating one is often just the questions asked at the start. Good questions do
    two things: they let you compare providers on what actually matters — scope — rather than on price
    alone, and they surface the assumptions that, left unspoken, turn into surprises once work begins.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/questions-to-ask-before-septic-installation-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
